()・・・  Houston woman was pumping gas Wednesday when a thief ran up and grabbed her designer purse and work bag off the passenger seat. She thinks the car was trailing her because she had just gone to Chase Bank down the street. (Thankfully, she made a deposit and not a withdrawal). The crooks must not have gotten what they were looking for because they tossed Christal Rowe’s stuff on the side of the road near Shepherd and 59. Keith, who often stands there with his sign, saw the items. He was raised not to go through a woman’s purse — so he called his girlfriend to look inside. They found Christal’s business card, called her and were able to get her belongings returned.Despite Keith being fairly new to the city, despite losing his job, and despite being on hard times — NOT ONE THING WAS MISSING. He says he wanted to do the right thing because it was “the godly thing to do.” When  interviewed him, he cried. She cried. She prayed over him and asked God to bless him. This holiday season, please help us change his life as he has changed ours through his honest spirit. He wears a size 13 shoe. He’s great at flooring, skilled in the janitorial field and ready to work. Rack your brain. If you know ANYONE who can empower him in any way, let Erica know.
